\pard\qc\sa240\f0\fs34\b THOG2 Enhanced Resume and Fork Specification Review\b0\par
\pard\qc\sa320\f0\fs22 Final completeness and consistency audit\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Status: Final audit complete against the implemented branch.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 1. Documents and code reviewed\b0\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Enhanced Resume and Fork Requirements Specification.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Enhanced Resume and Fork Implementation Plan.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Enhanced Resume and Fork Test Plan.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Existing compact-geometry, checkpoint, wrapper, naming, scheduler, and telemetry contracts.\par
\pard\sa100\li360\fi-240\f0\fs23 - Implemented Python modules, wrappers, checkpoint payloads, manifests, and tests.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 2. Total-step semantics\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 -n has one meaning in all modes: total optimizer steps for the run, not additional steps. Resume/fork require it explicitly and reject values less than or equal to completed_updates.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 This is consistent with the training loop condition completed_updates < max_updates and avoids invocation-relative ambiguity.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 3. Learning-rate consistency\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Resume evaluates the saved original schedule at completed_updates. A larger -n changes only the stop condition. Fork restart_cosine creates a new checkpointed phase ending at -n.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 The phrase first resumed step LR is precise: schedule parameters are immutable in resume, while the LR value may continue to evolve as the saved schedule is evaluated at later steps.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 4. Artifact terminology and identity\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 artifact_descriptor and artifact_name are distinct and used consistently. Runtime checkpoint paths use artifact_name because the directory includes the leading timestamp and optional fork suffix.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 n_, w_, k_, and S_ are excluded. Batch, accumulation, model dimensions, geometry, basis, orders, residual identity, dataset, and original peak-LR code remain visible.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 5. Material versus operational controls\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 dtype and non-finite controls are material and must match. Device, attention backend, activation checkpointing, checkpoint segment size, evaluation/log/checkpoint cadence, and instrumentation are operational.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 checkpoint_root is only a resolver input. It does not mutate inherited run configuration. eval_interval=0 consistently disables evaluation.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 6. Lifecycle and lineage\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 fresh, resume, and fork are disjoint. Resume reuses logical identity and outputs; fork creates a child identity and exactly one generated lineage suffix. Fork of fork increments generation while retaining the root timestamp.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 7. Checkpoint and telemetry consistency\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Checkpoint schema 3 is self-sufficient for model and optimizer recovery and contains lifecycle and phase state. The atomic manifest supports discovery and telemetry continuity without replacing checkpoint state.\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 W&B reuse is best effort and isolated from training state. TensorBoard and lifetime step axes remain continuous across resume.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 8. Compatibility scope\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 Earlier checkpoints and earlier artifact grammars are deliberately unsupported. No migration promise remains in the specification, implementation plan, tests, or code.\par
\pard\sa190\sb280\f0\fs29\b 9. Audit conclusion\b0\par
\pard\sa170\f0\fs23 The requirements, implementation plan, test plan, and implementation are internally consistent for the approved initial scope. No unresolved semantic contradiction was found in the final audit.\par
